resultset.description: While the UEE still controls the rights to the system overall, the four planets themselves were sold by the government to four megacorporations making them the only privately-owned worlds in the Empire. Though subject to the UEE’s Common Laws and standard penal code, the UEE does not police the region. Instead, private planetary security teams enforce the local law.
resultset.name: Stanton

celestial_objects.description: Jump Point
Jump Point

A terraforming error left the planet with an unnaturally dense cloud cover and a colder than average climate making it an ideal location for owner microTech to house its heat-sensitive computing and manufacturing centers.
celestial_objects.name: microTech

celestial_objects.description: A wealth of ore and other resources are mined on Hurston to manufacture the company’s line of munitions and weapons. Heavy industry has resulted in severe pollution across the planet.
celestial_objects.name: Hurston

celestial_objects.description: Buildings cover a majority of the planet’s surface with residential areas relegated to the poles while ArcCorp’s factories, business headquarters, financial and commercial districts are located in between.
celestial_objects.name: ArcCorp

celestial_objects.description: A low mass gas giant that features a breathable atmosphere at high altitudes. This was an ideal situation for ship manufacturer Crusader, who now occupies the planet’s floating platforms to build massive ships like the Starliner.
celestial_objects.name: Crusader

celestial_objects.description: Though Crusader Industries argues that the belt was part of their purchase of Stanton II from the UEE, the legal confusion and ensuing court case has created a massive wave of miners rushing to grab claims of their own.
celestial_objects.name: Aaron Halo

celestial_objects.description: Jump Point

Named after the youngest of the three siblings featured in the 25th century children’s tale, “A Gift for Baba,” this moon features over a hundred currently dormant volcanoes that are said to represent Cellin’s simmering anger.
celestial_objects.name: Cellin

celestial_objects.description: Named after the middle brother of the three siblings featured in the 25th century children’s tale, “A Gift for Baba,” this is the largest of Crusader’s moons. Daymar’s slightly eccentric orbit is said to represent his ease at getting lost in the story.
celestial_objects.name: Daymar

celestial_objects.description: Named after the oldest of the three siblings featured in the 25th century children’s tale, “A Gift for Baba,” this moon has a water-ice crust said to represent Yela’s cool and calculating mannerisms.
celestial_objects.name: Yela

celestial_objects.description: Located in the trade lanes above Crusader, Port Olisar offers a breathtaking view of the planet below. Owned and operated by Crusader Industries, Port Olisar acts as a gateway to the company’s vast planetary holdings and orbital shipyards.
A brand new outpost built to house an extended Crusader Security presence in this sector. It is expected to be open and operating soon.

Formerly Covalex’s prime shipping hub for the system, Gundo suffered a catastrophic accident that resulted in an explosion and the deaths of all the employees aboard the station. Covalex has since moved their operations to Orison directly.
This station is a franchise of Cry-Astro and provides facilities to restock and refuel a wide variety of ships.

Part of the Imperial Cartography Center, this research station is categorized as a Deep Space Scanning and AstroGraphical Station, one of the many turn-key facilities the UEE places in systems to casually sweep for jump points.
These communication stations are positioned around the area to help provide comm coverage.
This moon was named after the 3rd CEO of Hurston Dynamics, Arial Hurston, who was known for creating the controversial Life/Labor-style employee contract.
celestial_objects.name: Arial

celestial_objects.description: This moon was named after scientist Aberdeen Hurston who was credited with designing the company's first antimatter warhead.
celestial_objects.name: Aberdeen

celestial_objects.description: This moon was named after Hurston Dynamics CEO Magda Stanton who made the decision to purchase Stanton I from the UEE. Magda is the mother of current CEO “Colonel” Gavin E. Stanton.
celestial_objects.name: Magda

celestial_objects.description: This moon was named after Ita Hurston, who died during the First Tevarin War, as a reminder of why “the products Hurston Dynamics makes are so important.”
celestial_objects.name: Ita

celestial_objects.description: This icy moon features active cryogeysers and cryovolcanoes.
celestial_objects.name: Lyria

celestial_objects.description: The low density of Wala is particularly susceptible to tidal forces which result in the moon being noticeably prolate.
celestial_objects.name: Wala

celestial_objects.description: Named after the ancient Greek muse who inspires eloquence to supposedly remind those gazing upon the moon from microTech to 'strive for pure expression of thought.'
celestial_objects.name: Calliope

celestial_objects.description: Named after the ancient Greek muse of history to supposedly remind those gazing upon the moon from microTech to remember that 'their work stands on those who came before them.'
celestial_objects.name: Clio

celestial_objects.description: Named after the ancient Greek muse of music to supposedly remind those gazing upon the moon from microTech to be 'guided by the natural rhythm of the universe in their designs.'
celestial_objects.name: Euterpe
